{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783577122,"nonce":"ZQ4jbPG04MXx54Mm1z0eAm9kUUU=","message":"Phase 2 — **PR 2.0c (CTEs / `WITH` in a view body)** shipped as PR #94 (squash `2bca640`).\n\nThe third IR widening of the reverse-parser foundation (after 2.0 single-SELECT, 2.0a derived tables, 2.0b set ops). Adds `ViewBody::With { recursive, ctes, body }` + `CteModel`, so a view body carries ordinary and recursive CTEs, reconstructable on the render and reverse-parse paths across all three dialects. Per the maintainer-confirmed 2.0c/2.0d split, this is the **model / reverse-parser slice only** — the runtime query CTE path (`cte.rs` / `render.rs::write_cte_prefix`) is untouched; `render_with_prefix` is authored as the eventual shared renderer 2.0d will re-point onto.\n\nNotable resolutions (local codex, 4 rounds → clean):\n- **SQLite recursive-CTE arms render BARE** (`\u003canchor\u003e UNION ALL \u003crecursive\u003e`, no operand wrapping) on every dialect — a recursive-CTE grammar rejects a parenthesized arm; SQLite errors on both `(SELECT …)` and `SELECT * FROM (…)`. Verified against real `sqlite3` (a regression test publishes a recursive-CTE view into an in-memory DB and queries it).\n- **WITH-scoping** in `collect_body_sources` drops only *unqualified* sources matching a bound CTE name (a schema-qualified `public.dep` stays a real dependency).\n- **CTE self-reference detection** (render-side) likewise requires an unqualified name.\n- **Column-list fallback for set arms** (maintainer-approved): a declared column list is authoritative for a single-SELECT body but a fallback for a set arm, so the canonical recursive CTE with an un-aliased anchor (`SELECT 1 UNION ALL …`) lowers. Incidentally fixes the same shape for 2.0b set-op views.\n\nDeferred to **PR 2.0d** (runtime↔model CTE unification — pure dedup, no new capability): re-point `cte.rs`'s `CteDef::body()` onto `CteModel`/`ViewBody::Set`, route the runtime `write_cte_prefix` through the shared `render_with_prefix`, and delete `CteBody`/`render_cte_body`/`render_recursive_cte_body`.\n\nNext after 2.0d: per-backend introspection wiring 2.1 (PG) → 2.2 (MySQL) → 2.3 (SQLite).","files":null}]}